        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 19 at 11:51AM CDT until August 20 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the Extreme Heat Warning, dangerously hot conditions
with heat index values up to 112. For the Heat Advisory, heat
index values up to 107 expected.

* WHERE...In Arkansas, Phillips County. In Mississippi, Coahoma,
Panola, Quitman, Tallahatchie, and Tunica Counties.

* WHEN...For the Extreme Heat Warning, until 8 PM CDT this evening.
For the Heat Advisory, from 8 PM this evening to 8 PM CDT
Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat and high humidity events. Hot temperatures and high
humidity may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
